comments.body:
Bug: Pie chart Cell colors will be wrong when a legend item is hidden.

<Pie data={visibleData}> receives filtered data, but the <Cell> children iterate over chartData (unfiltered). Recharts matches Cell elements to data entries by positional index. When a user hides a series, visibleData has fewer entries than chartData, so the remaining slices get the wrong colors.

Example: chartData = [bug_fix(red), new_feature(blue), refactoring(purple)]. User hides "Bug Fix" -> visibleData = [new_feature, refactoring]. Cell[0] still has bug_fix's red, Cell[1] has new_feature's blue. Positional mapping: new_feature renders red (wrong), refactoring renders blue (wrong).

Fix: change chartData.map to visibleData.map here:

{visibleData.map((entry, index) => (
    <Cell
        key={`cell-${index}`}
        fill={COLORS[entry.task_type] || COLORS.unknown}
        className="hover:opacity-80 transition-opacity"
    />
))}

